dc:description: Soft brick red clay.  Rounded nozzle with large wick hole and broad channel on neck leading to discus.  On the rim are incised oblique rays set off by grooves on either side.  Raised band about discus.  Animal right on discus, two filling holes, solid grooved knob-like handle.  Small raised base ring with groove about outer edge connected with base of handle by ridge.  Incised stamp.  Crudely made.  Broken about wick hole and one of filling holes.
